<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-136-199 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 988 512</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  June 3 1991 v8 n11 p45(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The Netbios programming interface for Unix; API designed forpeer-to-peer network applications development. (applicationsprogramming interface) (tutorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Alulmbaugh, Wendell.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Netbios is a programming interface used for the development ofpeer-to-peer network applications.andP;  Its current specificationprovides expanded network commands for locating names on thenetwork and recording Netbios command execution.andP;  The NetworkControl Block (NCB) definition can be used to provide a wide rangeof applications, such as electronic mail, databases, andpoint-of-sale systems.andP;  A special protocol level is required forNetBios implementation on top of communications protocols; thereare several established local-area network (LAN) communicationsprotocols.andP;  Netbios API for Unix makes it easier to developnetwork applications and provides an effective way to achieveinteroperability between DOS, OS/2, and Unix.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   NETBIOS for UNIX System V (Communications software) (Usage)NetWare (Network operating system) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Applications Programming InterfaceApplications ProgrammingUNIXInteroperabilityLocal Area NetworksTutorial.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Making the network connection. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>